snippet: The experience is in stark contrast to reports of widespread technical problems that have hampered enrollment in the online marketplace run by the federal government.
abstract: Consumers are having more success signing up for health insurance through many state-run exchanges; experience is in stark contrast to reports of widespread technical problems that have hampered enrollment in online marketplace run by the federal government.

byline.original: By ROBERT PEAR and ABBY GOODNOUGH
byline.contributor: Katie Thomas and Jennifer Preston contributed reporting from New York.

headline.main: Uninsured Find More Success via Health Exchanges Run by States
